IN the INTEREST OF: A.M.Y., Plaintiff, Juvenile Officer, Respondent,
v.
T.S. (Mother), Appellant. WD 81047 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. Order filed: January 30, 2018 William E. Shull, Liberty, for Respondent. Joseph W. Vanover, Co-counsel for Respondent. Jack A. Lewis, North Kansas City, for Appellant. Before Division Three: Gary D. Witt, Presiding Judge, Lisa White Hardwick, Judge and Edward R. Ardini, Jr., Judge

ORDER

PER CURIAM:

Mother appeals the trial court's judgment finding that Child was in need of the care and protection of the court and removing Child from the home. Mother appeals, challenging the sufficiency of the evidence. Finding no error, we affirm. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. Rule 84.16(b).
